cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper deals with material segmentation using image context and local cues, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also uses image sequences, which can be considered as a form of computer graphics (cs.GR). The proposed method involves the use of residual encoding, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also involves building segment voting, which can be considered as a form of robotics (cs.RO).
